1
00:00:10,267 --> 00:00:12,833
<i>If you don't want Tonyo anymore,
just give him to us.</i>

2
00:00:12,967 --> 00:00:13,967
<i> Poor guy.</i>

3
00:00:14,100 --> 00:00:15,400
<i> Oh, come on, stop it.</i>

4
00:00:15,533 --> 00:00:16,767
<i> That's not a date.</i>

5
00:00:16,900 --> 00:00:17,900
<i> Lieutenant Conde?</i>

6
00:00:18,033 --> 00:00:20,567
<i>Bobby? You're here too?
Wow, what a small world.</i>

7
00:00:20,700 --> 00:00:21,733
<i> You're good, huh?</i>

8
00:00:21,867 --> 00:00:23,300
<i> You could win a Urian award.</i>

9
00:00:23,433 --> 00:00:25,367
<i>What if he's the killer
we're looking for?</i>

10
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:26,967
<i>He might already know
you're a cop.</i>

11
00:00:27,100 --> 00:00:28,900
<i>It's better if I stay close
to him</i>

12
00:00:29,033 --> 00:00:30,500
<i>so we can gather evidence,
right?</i>

13
00:00:30,633 --> 00:00:33,500
<i>Can you please connect me
to the office of the CEO?</i>

14
00:00:33,633 --> 00:00:36,767
<i>I'm sorry, Mr. Lee is out
of the country right now.</i>

15
00:00:36,933 --> 00:00:39,933
<i>Jared Lopez is not
the CEO of Add2Cart.</i>

16
00:00:40,067 --> 00:00:43,100
<i>For today's catwalk training,
we have a very special guest,</i>

17
00:00:43,233 --> 00:00:45,533
<i>the stunning
Mrs. Sophia Guerrero.</i>

18
00:00:45,667 --> 00:00:48,367
<i>I just want to see
what you all have.</i>

19
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:49,600
<i> Any volunteers?</i>

20
00:00:49,733 --> 00:00:52,033
<i>Speaking of the beauty
pageant...</i>

21
00:00:52,167 --> 00:00:54,933
<i>I saw Bobby got into
that beauty pageant.</i>

22
00:00:55,067 --> 00:00:56,400
<i>Good thing she still has time
to be a police officer.</i>

23
00:00:56,533 --> 00:00:59,033
<i> That's the walk of a loser.</i>

24
00:00:59,167 --> 00:01:04,233
<i>Like you didn't get a lot
of money from my husband.</i>

25
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:17,167
Wait!

26
00:01:17,300 --> 00:01:19,367
Didn't you already talk
to Add2Cart?

27
00:01:19,500 --> 00:01:23,300
They told you, right?
Jared isn't the CEO.

28
00:01:23,433 --> 00:01:24,700
That's the thing.

29
00:01:24,833 --> 00:01:26,233
So if he's really a fake,

30
00:01:26,367 --> 00:01:27,933
how did he manage
to bring the name Add2Cart

31
00:01:28,067 --> 00:01:29,067
to Miss Calabari?

32
00:01:29,200 --> 00:01:30,767
That's a public event.

33
00:01:30,900 --> 00:01:33,767
What? Does that mean he fooled
the whole organization?

34
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:36,133
Well, you have a point.

35
00:01:36,267 --> 00:01:39,400
So if their CEO
is really abroad,

36
00:01:39,533 --> 00:01:42,000
we'll look for another boss
we can talk to here.

37
00:01:42,167 --> 00:01:44,033
Hopefully they can help us.

38
00:01:44,167 --> 00:01:44,900
Okay.

39
00:01:46,933 --> 00:01:49,667
Bok, their receptionist
is a woman.

40
00:01:49,800 --> 00:01:52,500
Let me do the talking.
I'm an expert at this.

41
00:01:54,667 --> 00:01:55,800
Hi, Miss...

42
00:01:55,933 --> 00:01:57,567
Good afternoon, Sir.

43
00:01:57,700 --> 00:02:01,733
How do you redeem rewards here
at Add2Cart?

44
00:02:01,867 --> 00:02:05,367
That reward is only
for daily shoppers.

45
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:06,467
Daily?

46
00:02:07,667 --> 00:02:11,800
What about people like us who
only shop online once a month?

47
00:02:11,933 --> 00:02:13,467
Sorry, Sir.

48
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:16,933
Your standards are too high.
Every day?

49
00:02:17,100 --> 00:02:20,000
What's that? A millionaire?

50
00:02:20,133 --> 00:02:21,533
What, Bok? Are you done?

51
00:02:21,667 --> 00:02:24,067
Maybe you'll browse some more.

52
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:25,233
Go ahead.

53
00:02:26,833 --> 00:02:28,667
I'm Lieutenant Antonio Conde.

54
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:31,767
This is my partner,
Lieutenant Eric Garcia.

55
00:02:31,900 --> 00:02:34,733
We just want to ask
who we can talk to

56
00:02:34,867 --> 00:02:36,833
if your CEO isn't around.

57
00:02:36,967 --> 00:02:38,700
What's this about?

58
00:02:38,833 --> 00:02:40,400
It's confidential.

59
00:02:40,533 --> 00:02:43,200
We're investigating a case.

60
00:02:43,333 --> 00:02:45,533
Just the two of you
will be speaking, Sir?

61
00:02:45,667 --> 00:02:47,200
Yes, Ma'am.

62
00:02:47,367 --> 00:02:49,600
Which station are you from?

63
00:02:49,733 --> 00:02:51,567
Station 12.

64
00:02:51,700 --> 00:02:53,833
Can I check your IDs?

65
00:03:01,633 --> 00:03:04,000
I don't have my ID with me.
Just use his.

66
00:03:08,367 --> 00:03:10,167
Is that okay, Ma'am?

67
00:03:10,300 --> 00:03:13,367
So who can we talk to?

68
00:03:13,500 --> 00:03:16,100
The bosses aren't here today.

69
00:03:16,233 --> 00:03:18,167
I don't know when they'll be in.

70
00:03:19,533 --> 00:03:22,800
You asked us so many questions,
even took our ID,

71
00:03:22,967 --> 00:03:24,300
and turns out the people
we need to talk to

72
00:03:24,433 --> 00:03:25,733
aren't even here.

73
00:03:25,867 --> 00:03:28,200
Just for future reference.
Sorry.

74
00:03:28,333 --> 00:03:30,633
We'll let you know
when someone is available.

75
00:03:30,767 --> 00:03:32,200
Okay, thank you.

76
00:03:34,733 --> 00:03:37,500
Told you we'd just waste
our time here.

77
00:03:43,533 --> 00:03:45,933
Good afternoon, Ma'am.
I didn't know you're here.

78
00:03:46,067 --> 00:03:47,133
Good afternoon.

79
00:03:47,267 --> 00:03:49,033
Were you talking to police
officers earlier?

80
00:03:49,167 --> 00:03:49,933
Yes, Ma'am.

81
00:03:50,067 --> 00:03:51,467
What did they need?

82
00:04:23,767 --> 00:04:25,367
Okay, come on, ladies.

83
00:04:25,500 --> 00:04:28,733
You have to show me
that you're proud of your body.

84
00:04:28,900 --> 00:04:32,633
You have to show me
that you belong.

85
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:37,900
Thank you, Sandara.

86
00:04:39,700 --> 00:04:41,200
How about Tricia?

87
00:04:46,533 --> 00:04:47,600
Excuse me.

88
00:04:50,067 --> 00:04:52,400
Oh no, ladies,
you have to excuse me.

89
00:04:52,533 --> 00:04:54,000
I have to take this call.

90
00:04:54,133 --> 00:04:55,033
Come on.

91
00:04:59,833 --> 00:05:03,067
Hey, Bobby, sorry about earlier.

92
00:05:03,233 --> 00:05:04,333
For what?

93
00:05:04,467 --> 00:05:07,233
I was supposed to defend you
from the grumpy teacher.

94
00:05:07,367 --> 00:05:09,333
But Peach stopped me.

95
00:05:09,467 --> 00:05:11,233
She said we might
get targeted too.

96
00:05:11,367 --> 00:05:12,467
Hey, wait, Bobby.

97
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:16,233
You're making me look like
a worthless friend, Apple.

98
00:05:16,367 --> 00:05:17,367
Why? It's true though.

99
00:05:17,500 --> 00:05:18,167
No, it's not.

100
00:05:18,300 --> 00:05:19,333
That's enough.

101
00:05:19,467 --> 00:05:21,233
It's okay. No worries.

102
00:05:21,367 --> 00:05:23,800
You know, you did
the right thing.

103
00:05:23,933 --> 00:05:26,367
You didn't get involved
so you wouldn't get dragged in.

104
00:05:26,500 --> 00:05:27,300
Right.

105
00:05:27,433 --> 00:05:29,533
That's why I stopped her
earlier, Bobby.

106
00:05:29,667 --> 00:05:32,467
- Wow. You're so great.
- I'm really smart.

107
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:35,133
Wow, catwalk is really hard,
right?

108
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:40,433
Teresa, this is Apple and Peach.

109
00:05:40,567 --> 00:05:42,167
- Hello.
- Hi, Teresa.

110
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:43,600
You're so pretty...

111
00:05:43,733 --> 00:05:44,800
just like me.

112
00:05:44,933 --> 00:05:47,233
What are you saying?
You're even prettier than me.

113
00:05:47,367 --> 00:05:49,533
You two are prettier than me.

114
00:05:49,667 --> 00:05:51,467
I like her attitude.

115
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:53,233
- Correct.
- Honest.

116
00:05:53,367 --> 00:05:54,333
Right.

117
00:05:54,467 --> 00:05:56,100
We're all beautiful.

118
00:05:56,233 --> 00:05:58,667
And you saw how hard it was
for me earlier.

119
00:05:58,800 --> 00:06:01,467
Looks like we'll all struggle
with that catwalk.

120
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:04,233
Excuse me.

121
00:06:04,367 --> 00:06:05,433
Maybe just you guys.

122
00:06:05,567 --> 00:06:06,867
For me, this is easy.

123
00:06:08,767 --> 00:06:10,500
Let me show you how to do it.

124
00:06:13,267 --> 00:06:14,400
Okay, girls.

125
00:06:14,533 --> 00:06:15,700
Watch me.

126
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:36,800
You are the best, Charlie.

127
00:06:37,967 --> 00:06:39,500
Thank you, Maestra.

128
00:06:40,767 --> 00:06:43,100
Just call me "auntie."

129
00:06:43,233 --> 00:06:46,333
Maestra is only
for the newbies.

130
00:06:46,467 --> 00:06:48,367
Thank you, Auntie.

131
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:49,467
Of course.

132
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:52,533
Anyway, ladies, I have to go,

133
00:06:52,667 --> 00:06:58,767
but if you want more lessons,
Charlie can do it, okay?

134
00:06:58,900 --> 00:07:01,700
Ladies, let's give Ma'am Sophia
a round of applause.

135
00:07:03,667 --> 00:07:06,700
Thank you so much.
You've still got it, Madam.

136
00:07:06,833 --> 00:07:08,600
Just say it, Francis.

137
00:07:08,733 --> 00:07:11,567
Well, I think she is
the all-time best

138
00:07:11,700 --> 00:07:13,467
of Miss Calabari.

139
00:07:15,100 --> 00:07:16,333
I know.

140
00:07:16,467 --> 00:07:18,767
All right, goodbye, everyone.

141
00:07:27,333 --> 00:07:30,433
Bobby, if you want lessons,
I'm here, okay?

142
00:07:45,533 --> 00:07:46,267
Torres!

143
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:48,867
Bautista, De Jesus!

144
00:07:49,033 --> 00:07:51,033
- Sir.
- Sir.

145
00:07:54,667 --> 00:07:56,867
I'm assigning a case to you.

146
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:58,400
What case, Sir?

147
00:07:58,533 --> 00:08:03,200
Lieutenant Robles' sniper,
still hasn't been found.

148
00:08:03,333 --> 00:08:06,733
Bautista, I want you to take
the lead...

149
00:08:08,567 --> 00:08:13,767
so we'll know if you learned
anything from Garcia.

150
00:08:13,900 --> 00:08:15,000
Copy, Sir.

151
00:08:15,133 --> 00:08:16,000
Is that clear?

152
00:08:16,133 --> 00:08:17,533
Yes, Sir.

153
00:08:17,667 --> 00:08:18,400
Okay.

154
00:08:19,767 --> 00:08:22,333
Nice one, Bautista. Well done.

155
00:08:22,500 --> 00:08:26,067
Come on, stop it.
I'm already feeling pressured.

156
00:08:26,200 --> 00:08:28,800
Feels like if I mess up,

157
00:08:28,933 --> 00:08:31,267
even Sir Garcia's reputation
will be ruined.

158
00:08:32,367 --> 00:08:33,300
Come on.

159
00:08:33,433 --> 00:08:34,667
Don't feel pressured.

160
00:08:34,800 --> 00:08:36,533
We'll help you.

161
00:08:36,667 --> 00:08:37,700
Right, De Jesus?

162
00:08:37,833 --> 00:08:40,433
Torres is right.
We'll plan it out.

163
00:08:40,567 --> 00:08:41,900
Okay, thank you.

164
00:08:42,033 --> 00:08:45,167
Better yet, let's start
with Lieutenant Robles' autopsy.

165
00:08:45,300 --> 00:08:46,933
Let's call Doc Cecilia.

166
00:08:47,067 --> 00:08:48,700
- Okay, let's go.
- Let's go.

167
00:08:58,300 --> 00:09:01,033
Those training are really
exhausting, right?

168
00:09:01,167 --> 00:09:02,800
So tiring, Apple.

169
00:09:02,933 --> 00:09:04,033
Exactly.

170
00:09:04,167 --> 00:09:07,433
You know, I'm hungry.
Come on, Bobby, let's eat.

171
00:09:07,567 --> 00:09:10,033
I'm still good.
You guys go ahead.

172
00:09:10,167 --> 00:09:12,000
- Are you sure?
- I'm good.

173
00:09:12,133 --> 00:09:14,267
- Let's go, Teresa, let's eat.
- Okay.

174
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:15,300
- Go ahead.
- We'll eat first.

175
00:09:15,433 --> 00:09:16,533
Okay, go.

176
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:23,367
Bobby.

177
00:09:25,767 --> 00:09:27,267
- What?
- Oh my...

178
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:30,800
It's so hard to be embarrassed
in front of a crowd, right?

179
00:09:30,967 --> 00:09:32,533
It's your fault.

180
00:09:32,667 --> 00:09:35,067
You insisted on competing
with me.

181
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:36,967
Now, you got humiliated.

182
00:09:37,100 --> 00:09:39,333
Oh, Charlie.

183
00:09:39,467 --> 00:09:42,100
Please. I don't have time
for that.

184
00:09:42,233 --> 00:09:44,400
I'm here to focus on the case.

185
00:09:44,533 --> 00:09:45,933
Of course.

186
00:09:46,067 --> 00:09:47,867
But how will you solve the case

187
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:49,200
if you get eliminated
right away?

188
00:09:52,133 --> 00:09:54,400
Well, I'm here anyway.

189
00:09:54,533 --> 00:09:58,333
And no one expects you
to go far.

190
00:09:58,467 --> 00:10:02,267
Don't worry.
I'll finish this case for you.

191
00:10:02,433 --> 00:10:03,900
Whatever.

192
00:10:04,033 --> 00:10:07,333
Let's just stay observant
of everything we see,

193
00:10:07,467 --> 00:10:08,967
especially those wearing
hoodies.

194
00:10:09,100 --> 00:10:11,533
One of them could be the killer.

195
00:10:11,667 --> 00:10:14,100
All right. You're exhausting
to talk to.

196
00:10:14,233 --> 00:10:15,467
Whatever.

197
00:10:23,167 --> 00:10:26,600
Don't you just hate that girl?

198
00:10:26,733 --> 00:10:28,400
Ma'am, you're still here.

199
00:10:29,433 --> 00:10:30,867
I forgot something.

200
00:10:32,633 --> 00:10:36,267
That girl really annoys me.
Such a show-off.

201
00:10:37,533 --> 00:10:41,400
Do you want me to eliminate her
in the first round?

202
00:10:42,933 --> 00:10:44,333
Can you?

203
00:10:44,467 --> 00:10:45,733
You can do that?

204
00:10:45,867 --> 00:10:46,833
Of course!

205
00:10:46,967 --> 00:10:48,733
I'll be one of the judges.

206
00:10:48,867 --> 00:10:50,700
Sure, do it.

207
00:10:53,100 --> 00:10:54,767
I can...

208
00:10:56,467 --> 00:10:57,733
but I wouldn't.

209
00:10:58,833 --> 00:11:00,033
Why?

210
00:11:00,167 --> 00:11:04,333
Because I want her to reach
the finals.

211
00:11:04,467 --> 00:11:05,667
What?

212
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:12,733
Then I'll humiliate her
in front of all of Calabari.

213
00:11:15,033 --> 00:11:17,933
Just stay under my wing, Dear.

214
00:11:18,067 --> 00:11:20,000
You'll learn a lot.

215
00:11:20,967 --> 00:11:22,700
- Bye.
- Bye, Auntie.

216
00:11:32,433 --> 00:11:33,600
Good morning, Madame.

217
00:11:33,733 --> 00:11:35,133
Good morning.

218
00:11:35,267 --> 00:11:37,000
All right, just let me know
if you need anything,

219
00:11:37,133 --> 00:11:39,600
my office is here to help you.

220
00:11:39,733 --> 00:11:41,467
Cecilia.

221
00:11:41,633 --> 00:11:42,833
Just a moment, okay?

222
00:11:42,967 --> 00:11:44,600
What are you doing here?

223
00:11:46,300 --> 00:11:47,900
I came to visit you.

224
00:11:48,033 --> 00:11:49,533
Do you want to have lunch?

225
00:11:49,667 --> 00:11:51,900
My meeting's not until later.
Come on, let's go.

226
00:11:52,033 --> 00:11:53,533
Sorry, Glen, I have work.

227
00:11:54,567 --> 00:11:55,900
Where are you going?

228
00:11:56,033 --> 00:11:57,900
To Station 12.

229
00:11:58,033 --> 00:11:59,333
Station 12?

230
00:11:59,467 --> 00:12:02,533
You should've come with me then.
I just came from there.

231
00:12:03,933 --> 00:12:05,467
What were you doing there?

232
00:12:08,367 --> 00:12:11,667
Cecilia, relax, okay?
I didn't do anything wrong.

233
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:14,533
I just talked to the Major
about Miss Calabari.

234
00:12:14,700 --> 00:12:16,433
I want things to run smoothly.

235
00:12:16,567 --> 00:12:18,967
We need to be on the same page.
That's all.

236
00:12:21,867 --> 00:12:25,000
Okay, I have to go.
I'll see you later, okay?

237
00:12:29,633 --> 00:12:31,333
Cecilia, wait.

238
00:12:34,200 --> 00:12:35,833
You still love me, right?

239
00:12:37,933 --> 00:12:39,500
What are you saying?

240
00:12:41,033 --> 00:12:42,300
Just make sure, okay?

241
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:45,167
I need you on my side now.

242
00:12:48,533 --> 00:12:49,800
Let me ask you again.

243
00:12:51,333 --> 00:12:53,100
You still love me, right?

244
00:12:58,900 --> 00:12:59,667
Good.

245
00:13:01,700 --> 00:13:02,833
Take care.

246
00:13:12,400 --> 00:13:14,367
- What do you want to eat?
- Salad...

247
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:16,467
- Salad?
- With pork chop on top.

248
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:18,067
Can we just have pancit malabon?

249
00:13:19,167 --> 00:13:21,100
- With pork chop on top?
- Bobby!

250
00:13:21,267 --> 00:13:22,067
Sir.

251
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:23,700
I've been looking for you.

252
00:13:23,833 --> 00:13:25,133
How's training?

253
00:13:25,267 --> 00:13:28,267
I heard Miss Sophia
gave you a hard time.

254
00:13:29,700 --> 00:13:30,733
That's okay.

255
00:13:30,867 --> 00:13:31,967
I'm used to it.

256
00:13:33,100 --> 00:13:34,500
I'm not worried.

257
00:13:34,633 --> 00:13:36,500
I know you can handle things
like that.

258
00:13:39,067 --> 00:13:42,367
Bobby, you're the daughter
of the former mayor of Calabari?

259
00:13:45,867 --> 00:13:47,267
I'm very sorry for your loss.

260
00:13:49,867 --> 00:13:51,833
Actually, I know
you're probably tired

261
00:13:51,967 --> 00:13:54,333
from everything you've done,
but...

262
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:56,933
I was hoping to invite you
to dinner, if that's okay.

263
00:13:58,367 --> 00:13:59,900
Sir, I'll have to check.

264
00:14:00,033 --> 00:14:02,267
Because I need to go home.

265
00:14:02,400 --> 00:14:04,867
My grandmother has dementia.

266
00:14:06,500 --> 00:14:11,600
Is that so? Okay, okay.
Go home first.

267
00:14:11,733 --> 00:14:12,267
We can go next time.

268
00:14:12,400 --> 00:14:13,367
That's more important,

269
00:14:13,500 --> 00:14:15,600
so you can take care
of your grandmother.

270
00:14:15,733 --> 00:14:18,333
I've been thinking of hiring
a caregiver.

271
00:14:21,033 --> 00:14:22,867
That's fine, but...

272
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:25,700
you know, Bobby,
it's still more important

273
00:14:25,833 --> 00:14:29,133
that we're the ones taking care
of our loved ones, right?

274
00:14:30,267 --> 00:14:31,833
Okay, Sir. Thank you, Sir.

275
00:14:39,133 --> 00:14:41,133
So, what's your plan?

276
00:14:41,267 --> 00:14:43,200
You'll wait for Jared
to come out,

277
00:14:43,333 --> 00:14:46,600
then tail him once he's outside?

278
00:14:49,933 --> 00:14:51,400
Hold on...

279
00:14:51,533 --> 00:14:52,833
Why?

280
00:14:52,967 --> 00:14:56,567
I know Jared is suspicious,

281
00:14:56,700 --> 00:15:02,767
but that doesn't mean he's the
killer of Donabel Custodio.

282
00:15:04,500 --> 00:15:06,233
What do you think of me, Bok?

283
00:15:06,367 --> 00:15:14,133
No, I just want to make sure
your head is clear.

284
00:15:14,267 --> 00:15:15,967
What are you talking about?

285
00:15:16,100 --> 00:15:20,100
I'm just making sure your
decision-making isn't clouded.

286
00:15:22,633 --> 00:15:29,067
I'm just saying, you shouldn't
mix jealousy with work.

287
00:15:29,200 --> 00:15:31,867
I'm not jealous, Bok.

288
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:33,700
Why would I be jealous?

289
00:15:34,967 --> 00:15:39,267
See? He can't even convince
himself.

290
00:15:39,400 --> 00:15:40,567
What did you say?

291
00:15:40,700 --> 00:15:44,300
That tree is beautiful. I want
to plant one like that at home.

292
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:00,633
Hello?

293
00:16:00,767 --> 00:16:05,000
Two police officers were here
earlier asking about you.

294
00:16:05,133 --> 00:16:06,233
<i> What should we do?</i>

295
00:16:07,267 --> 00:16:08,767
Yes, I know.

296
00:16:08,933 --> 00:16:11,467
I'll be careful.
No one will find out the truth.

297
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:12,333
Okay.

298
00:16:20,633 --> 00:16:23,167
Sorry, I just forgot something.

299
00:16:35,433 --> 00:16:36,400
This is the shade
that suits you.

300
00:16:36,533 --> 00:16:37,933
This is what you should put
on your lips.

301
00:16:38,067 --> 00:16:38,933
So unfair!

302
00:16:39,067 --> 00:16:40,333
- It suits you better.
- Me too.

303
00:16:40,467 --> 00:16:41,733
Thank you, Selena.

304
00:16:41,900 --> 00:16:42,767
It's nothing.

305
00:16:42,900 --> 00:16:44,967
You know, you should join
the pageant too.

306
00:16:45,100 --> 00:16:46,900
You'd definitely get in
right away.

307
00:16:47,033 --> 00:16:49,400
Yes, Sis, you should join.

308
00:16:49,533 --> 00:16:51,233
Some of the other contestants
here aren't even that pretty.

309
00:16:51,367 --> 00:16:52,833
- Hey, don't say that.
- But you know, Selena,

310
00:16:52,967 --> 00:16:54,400
you're already a winner to us.

311
00:16:54,533 --> 00:16:55,833
You're already beautiful,

312
00:16:55,967 --> 00:16:58,100
your hair's so long,
and you've got a love life.

313
00:16:58,233 --> 00:16:59,800
- Exactly!
- Keep it low.

314
00:16:59,933 --> 00:17:02,167
That's not true,
we're not even together yet.

315
00:17:02,300 --> 00:17:03,467
- What about Sir Eric?
- What about Sir Eric?

316
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:07,100
Selena...

317
00:17:08,733 --> 00:17:10,433
Sir...

318
00:17:12,167 --> 00:17:14,900
No, we're just talking!

319
00:17:15,067 --> 00:17:17,433
We're just in the talking stage,
Ma'am Bobby.

320
00:17:17,567 --> 00:17:20,167
- Really?
- Yes! Don't believe them.

321
00:17:20,300 --> 00:17:22,067
These gossipmongers...

322
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:24,233
How about you and Sir Tonyo,
Ma'am Bobby?

323
00:17:24,367 --> 00:17:25,833
Are you talking again?

324
00:17:28,200 --> 00:17:29,200
No.

325
00:17:29,333 --> 00:17:32,700
I'm just focusing
on Miss Calabari.

326
00:17:32,833 --> 00:17:36,333
Bobby, who is Tonyo?
Is he your boyfriend?

327
00:17:36,467 --> 00:17:37,667
Yes!

328
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:40,300
No!

329
00:17:40,433 --> 00:17:41,833
Hey, you guys!

330
00:17:43,033 --> 00:17:46,300
- Just go do your makeup.
- So you have a boyfriend.

331
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:56,967
We've been here for a while now.

332
00:17:58,033 --> 00:18:00,133
So, are we really going
to wait for Jared?

333
00:18:00,267 --> 00:18:02,333
Who knows what kind
of activities

334
00:18:02,467 --> 00:18:04,767
they're doing in there.

335
00:18:04,900 --> 00:18:06,600
What, are you bored?

336
00:18:06,733 --> 00:18:08,700
Just buy us something to eat.

337
00:18:10,833 --> 00:18:11,500
Okay.

338
00:18:13,533 --> 00:18:15,667
I thought your credit limit
was high?

339
00:18:15,800 --> 00:18:18,733
The stores here
don't accept cards.

340
00:18:18,867 --> 00:18:20,533
And this was your idea.

341
00:18:24,533 --> 00:18:27,400
Well, next time,
it's your turn, okay?

342
00:18:28,667 --> 00:18:29,667
If it's my idea.

343
00:18:29,800 --> 00:18:30,933
This was your idea.

344
00:18:58,167 --> 00:18:59,300
Good day, Mayor.

345
00:19:15,433 --> 00:19:16,533
I'm here already.

346
00:19:34,367 --> 00:19:35,700
Sir, good afternoon, Sir.

347
00:19:35,833 --> 00:19:39,233
Boss, do you know where
the Mayor is headed?

348
00:19:39,367 --> 00:19:42,067
Sir, to the Miss Calabari event,
Sir.

349
00:19:42,200 --> 00:19:43,833
At the pool area, Sir.

350
00:19:44,967 --> 00:19:46,733
- Thank you.
- Welcome, Sir.

351
00:19:50,700 --> 00:19:51,500
Ladies!

352
00:19:52,533 --> 00:19:55,500
If you think you're already good
at walking

353
00:19:55,633 --> 00:19:57,667
and doing the catwalk,

354
00:19:57,800 --> 00:20:05,300
in reality, it's hard to walk in
heels while people are watching.

355
00:20:05,467 --> 00:20:08,700
Even if you're used
to wearing bikinis,

356
00:20:08,833 --> 00:20:11,400
the pressure is different.

357
00:20:11,533 --> 00:20:14,533
When a lot of people
are looking at you

358
00:20:14,667 --> 00:20:16,867
and you're in your swimsuits,

359
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:20,633
it brings down
your confidence level

360
00:20:20,767 --> 00:20:22,967
during the swimsuit competition.

361
00:20:23,100 --> 00:20:26,200
For now, you'll walk the runway
with your swimsuits

362
00:20:26,333 --> 00:20:29,300
until I see the level
of confidence

363
00:20:29,433 --> 00:20:31,667
the judges want to see.

364
00:20:31,800 --> 00:20:33,267
Is that clear?

365
00:20:33,400 --> 00:20:35,033
- Yes, Auntie.
- Yes, Madame!

366
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:37,233
All right! Shall we begin?

367
00:21:17,100 --> 00:21:18,367
No one?

368
00:21:18,500 --> 00:21:20,167
Going once...

369
00:21:21,733 --> 00:21:24,067
Going twice...

370
00:21:25,633 --> 00:21:26,867
Sold!

371
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:35,333
Easy money!

372
00:21:52,067 --> 00:21:53,467
Go, Apple!

373
00:21:59,500 --> 00:22:00,867
There you go! Go, girl!

374
00:22:08,700 --> 00:22:11,833
<i>That's what you shouldn't do,
okay?</i>

375
00:22:11,967 --> 00:22:14,000
<i>Let Charlie be your role model.</i>

376
00:22:19,633 --> 00:22:21,467
You know, girls...

377
00:22:21,600 --> 00:22:23,200
you're all doing okay...

378
00:22:24,467 --> 00:22:26,567
except for one.

379
00:22:26,700 --> 00:22:27,700
Bobby!

380
00:22:30,300 --> 00:22:31,933
Step forward, please.

381
00:22:38,833 --> 00:22:41,167
Let me see your walk, please.

382
00:22:58,500 --> 00:22:59,667
Oh my...

383
00:22:59,800 --> 00:23:00,833
Stop!

384
00:23:02,933 --> 00:23:05,900
Hold on. I can't take it
anymore.

385
00:23:09,733 --> 00:23:12,333
This is not working.

386
00:23:12,467 --> 00:23:13,767
Is there something wrong
with your legs?

387
00:23:13,900 --> 00:23:15,400
Why do you walk like that?

388
00:23:15,533 --> 00:23:16,700
You look bowlegged.

389
00:23:16,833 --> 00:23:17,767
Are you bowlegged?

390
00:23:20,400 --> 00:23:22,733
Face that way.

391
00:23:25,200 --> 00:23:28,867
All right, Ladies,
if you walk like her,

392
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:30,967
you're definitely going to lose.

393
00:23:32,400 --> 00:23:35,600
Let me show you how it's done.

394
00:23:35,733 --> 00:23:38,533
Bobby, step back a little.

395
00:23:43,533 --> 00:23:45,100
What?

396
00:23:45,233 --> 00:23:49,267
Not enough.
I said move to the left.

397
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:57,633
What's with you?
I told you to move to the left!

398
00:23:57,800 --> 00:23:59,133
Ma'am!

399
00:24:03,667 --> 00:24:04,467
Auntie!

400
00:24:06,800 --> 00:24:08,200
Hold me!

401
00:24:25,033 --> 00:24:28,867
I can feel that tonight
is going to be a great night

402
00:24:29,033 --> 00:24:30,133
for all of us.

403
00:24:30,267 --> 00:24:33,600
No one knows yet about the
prostitution we're involved in.

404
00:24:33,733 --> 00:24:35,733
But just make sure, okay?

405
00:24:35,867 --> 00:24:38,600
Don't get caught
for killing Donabel.

406
00:24:38,733 --> 00:24:40,067
Are you looking for me?

407
00:24:40,200 --> 00:24:42,333
Let's give those two something
to keep them busy.

408
00:24:42,467 --> 00:24:43,667
They want a suspect?

409
00:24:43,800 --> 00:24:45,633
I'll plant a suspect.

410
00:24:45,767 --> 00:24:48,900
You know I suspect the Mayor and
Ma'am Sophia had me beaten up,

411
00:24:49,033 --> 00:24:49,600
right?

412
00:24:49,733 --> 00:24:51,167
I want to know the truth.

413
00:24:51,300 --> 00:24:54,567
We can't mix our personal issues
with our work.

414
00:24:54,700 --> 00:24:57,200
I know this might be too soon
for you, but...

415
00:24:57,333 --> 00:24:59,133
I like you, Bobby.

416
00:24:59,267 --> 00:25:00,000
Hands up!

417
00:25:00,133 --> 00:25:01,367
Jared Lopez.

418
00:25:01,500 --> 00:25:02,333
Sir!

419
00:25:02,500 --> 00:25:04,033
I knew it! I was right
about this jerk!
